## How This System Works

This folder is your brain. Each top-level directory has one purpose. When something new needs a home, the right folder is usually obvious.

```
AI-OS/
|
| -- Control files (read in full each session) --
|-- CLAUDE.md ............ Identity, protocols, decision rules
|-- risks.md ............. Risk flags — read before important actions
|-- MEMORY.md ............ Long-term memory (user-triggered writes only)
|
| -- Working folders (grow with content) --
|-- memory/ .............. Decisions, sessions, transcripts
|   |-- decisions/         Episodic: what happened, why, what was learned
|   |-- short-term/        Working memory (consolidated nightly)
|   |   \-- transcripts/   Archived session transcripts (from hooks)
|
|-- learning/ ............ How the system corrects itself
|   |-- corrections.md     What went wrong
|   |-- patterns.md        What works (extracted from corrections)
|   \-- skill-feedback/    Per-skill feedback + improvement history
|
|-- knowledge/ ........... People, companies, markets
|   |-- people/            Individuals
|   |-- companies/         Organizations
|   \-- market/            Market digests, competitor notes
|
|-- routines/ ............ Habits, briefings, recurring work
|   |-- daily/             Morning briefing, triage
|   |-- weekly/            Planning, retro
|   \-- on-demand/         Research, prep
|
|-- projects/ ............ Active initiatives, each with its own CLAUDE.md
|   \-- [project]/         Project context + memory
|
|-- blueprints/ .......... Templates and reusable how-tos
|-- voice/ ............... Brand, voice, communication style
|-- system/ .............. Goals, architecture, vital signs
\-- archive/ ............. Inactive but searchable
```

### Adding something new

| Want | Where |
|---|---|
| Remember a recurring situation | `MEMORY.md` (ask first) |
| Avoid a known mistake | `risks.md` |
