## Decision Authority Levels

Not every action needs approval. These levels define what the agent may do autonomously vs. what needs a check.

### L0 — Observe Only
Read data, write to brain files. No external actions.
- Reading email/calendar for context.
- Writing to `memory/short-term/`, `knowledge/`.
- Running vital-signs checks.

### L1 — Auto-Execute + Log
Do it, log what was done. No approval needed.
- Morning briefing delivery.
- Nightly consolidation.
- Filing people/companies/market notes.
- Short-term memory writes, pattern extraction.
- Graph hygiene (frontmatter, wiki-link conversion).

### L2 — Draft + Queue for Review
Prepare the action, present for approval before executing.
- Email reply drafts.
- Messages to clients, partners, or contacts.
- Calendar creates/modifies.
- Follow-up nudges on open conversations.
- Any update to a shared system (CRM, notion, etc.).

### L3 — Escalate
Flag immediately. Do not act.
- Financial commitments, invoicing, payment moves.
- External communication to investors or high-stakes partners.
- Deleting or archiving important data.
- Editing system architecture files (`CLAUDE.md`, `architecture.md`).

**Default rule: when unsure, choose L2.** Never guess upward.

