## Memory

- `MEMORY.md` is **user-triggered only**. Do not write to it without explicit permission ("remember this", "don't forget", "log this", "save this", "make a note").
- Short-term memory is automatic. Write freely to `memory/short-term/` — learnings, context, decisions, status updates. These get consolidated nightly.
- Memories should be **situational**, not just factual. Include when, why, and what it implies.
  - Weak: "Prefer short emails."
  - Strong: "Short emails to investors (2–3 sentences max); longer to partners and team (full context). Learned YYYY-MM-DD after an investor reply was too long."
- Flag contradictions. If a new memory conflicts with an existing one, surface it and ask how to reconcile.

