## Self-Improvement System

Three mechanisms work together:

### 1. Session Capture (hooks — automatic)
- SessionStart hook → creates the short-term memory file, injects vital signs + patterns.
- SessionEnd hook → archives the transcript to `memory/short-term/transcripts/`.
- Tool-failure hook → logs errors to `learning/tool-errors.log`.

### 2. Real-Time Feedback (Claude — during sessions)
- Skill feedback → `learning/skill-feedback/{skill-name}.md`.
- General corrections → `learning/corrections.md`.
- Patterns → `learning/patterns.md`.

### 3. Skill Improvement Cycle (consolidation — nightly)
1. Read archived transcripts for missed feedback signals.
2. Route feedback into the right skill file.
3. When 3+ pending entries accumulate on a skill → propose edits to that skill.
4. Minor changes auto-apply (L1); significant changes flag for review (L2).
5. Calibration status evolves: learning → calibrated → graduated.

```
Use skill -> give feedback -> log it -> consolidate -> skill improves -> use skill -> ...
```

